{
  "id": "019cf122-3dca-7423-a71b-05b3764679b4",
  "content": "## Session 2026-03-15 — Work Summary\n\n### Completed fixes (committed + pushed to both repos)\n\n#### Fix 1: corvia-server crash (CRITICAL — was blocking everything)\n- Root cause: corvia.toml had wrong Qwen3 model filename: `Qwen3-8B-Q4_K_M.gguf`\n- Fix: renamed to `Qwen_Qwen3-8B-Q4_K_M.gguf` (bartowski uses org prefix in filenames)\n- Also cleared a stale HuggingFace download lock file\n- Status: LIVE — corvia-server is healthy, qwen3 loaded on CUDA GPU\n\n#### Fix 2: Playwright Chrome missing from Docker image\n- Root cause: `COPY --from=playwright /ms-playwright` only copied ffmpeg, no browser\n- Fix: Dockerfile now runs `npx playwright install chrome --with-deps` (amd64) or `chromium` (arm64)\n- Chrome installed at runtime in current container: /opt/google/chrome/chrome\n- Status: LIVE in current container, will be in image after rebuild\n\n#### Fix 3: Claude not working on first connect in fresh containers\n- Root cause: .claude/settings.local.json is gitignored but holds `enabledMcpjsonServers: [corvia, playwright]`. Missing in fresh containers → MCP servers not auto-enabled → corvia_search fails → CLAUDE.md first-step requirement breaks\n- Fix: post-start.sh now bootstraps settings.local.json if missing/incomplete (same pattern as .mcp.json). Also removed spurious `\"permissions\":{\"allow\":[]}` from the file.\n- Status: LIVE\n\n#### Fix 4: OpenVINO EP for embedding (source code done, WAITING ON RELEASE)\n- Goal: Use Intel iGPU (OpenVINO EP) for nomic-embed-text embedding, keep NVIDIA CUDA for qwen3 chat — both GPUs simultaneously\n- Hardware confirmed: /dev/dri/card0+card1, libopenvino.so.2025.3, corvia-inference already detects `cuda=true openvino=true`\n- Code changes in repos/corvia (committed, pushed to GitHub master):\n  - crates/corvia-common/src/config.rs: added `embedding_backend: String` field to InferenceConfig (serde default=\"\")\n  - crates/corvia-kernel/src/inference_provisioner.rs: load_models + ensure_ready now accept `embedding_backend` param; sends it for embedding LoadModelRequest, keeps `backend` for chat\n  - crates/corvia-cli/src/main.rs: both ensure_ready call sites updated to pass `&config.inference.embedding_backend`\n- corvia.toml: `embedding_backend = \"openvino\"` added (ready for when new binary is installed)\n- **BLOCKER**: Needs a new GitHub release of repos/corvia so install_binaries downloads binary with the new InferenceConfig field. No CUDA toolkit in container so can't build locally with --features cuda.\n- rebuild.py updated to include `--features corvia-inference/cuda` for future builds when CUDA toolkit is available\n\n#### Fix 5: Docker-outside-of-Docker (WAITING ON CONTAINER REBUILD)\n- docker-compose.yml: mounts /var/run/docker.sock from host\n- Dockerfile: installs docker-ce-cli, creates docker group\n- Docker CLI already installed in current container (Docker 29.3.0) but socket not mounted until rebuild\n- **ACTION NEEDED**: VS Code \"Rebuild Container\" to activate\n\n#### Fix 6: Port forwarding\n- devcontainer.json: added 8030 (corvia-inference gRPC) to forwardPorts\n- Port map: 8020 REST+MCP ✓, 8021 dashboard ✓, 8030 gRPC (new) ✓, 8050 playwright-mcp (container-only), 11434 ollama ✓\n- No host port conflicts: docker-compose.yml has no `ports:` mappings; container ports isolated\n\n### Next steps to complete\n1. Publish new corvia repo release (tag v0.4.4 or next) → CI builds binary with embedding_backend field\n2. Rebuild devcontainer (VS Code \"Rebuild Container\") → activates Docker socket + Chrome in image + port 8030\n3. After rebuild: verify `corvia-dev status` shows all services healthy\n4. After new binary installs: verify corvia-inference logs show `backend=openvino` for embedding\n5. Test docker build from inside container: `docker build -t corvia-devcontainer-test .devcontainer/`\n\n### Port conflict guidance for dogfeed testing\n- No conflicts for `docker build` (no ports exposed)\n- For `docker run` with port access: use offset ports e.g. `-p 9020:8020 -p 9021:8021`\n- VS Code devcontainer forwarding doesn't bind host ports → no conflict with test containers\n",
  "source_version": "mcp",
